---
/**
 * Short explainer for visitors who don't already know pi.
 *
 * Lives between the Hero and the BigIdea section so the narrative flows:
 *   Hero (hook) → WhatIsPi (context) → BigIdea (the dashboard's role) → Why → …
 */
---

<section
  id="what-is-pi"
  class="relative mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-6 md:pt-8 pb-16 md:pb-20"
>
  <div
    class="pi-gradient-border rounded-2xl bg-pi-surface/60 backdrop-blur-sm p-6 md:p-10"
    data-reveal
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[auto,1fr] gap-6 md:gap-10 items-start">
      <div class="flex md:flex-col items-center md:items-start gap-3">
        <div
          class="flex h-14 w-14 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-pi-accent/25 to-pi-accent2/15 border border-pi-accent/30 font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-pi-accent shadow-pi-glow"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >
          π
        </div>
        <div class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-pi-accent">
          First, what's pi?
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4 text-pi-muted leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-pi-fg font-semibold underline decoration-pi-accent/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-pi-accent"
            >pi</a
          >
          is an open-source
          <span class="text-pi-fg font-medium">coding agent CLI</span> — a tiny
          terminal program that turns any LLM (Claude, GPT, Gemini, open models…)
          into an agent that can read your code, edit files, run commands, and
          talk to you as you work.
        </p>

        <p>
          You run it in a project folder, it picks up your files, and you
          collaborate with it like a very fast pair-programmer. It's
          model-agnostic, extensible through skills and packages, and ships with
          an interactive TUI. Each conversation with the agent is called a
          <strong class="text-pi-fg font-medium">session</strong>.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong class="text-pi-fg">pi-dashboard</strong> — the thing on this
          page — <em>does not replace pi.</em> It sits alongside it: a bridge
          extension inside every session forwards events to a local server,
          which streams them to any browser. Your TUI keeps working; the
          dashboard just adds eyes, hands, and reach.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-2">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full border border-pi-border/80 bg-pi-surface/60 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-pi-fg hover:border-pi-accent/60 transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="text-pi-accent">↗</span> pi repo
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono#readme"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full border border-pi-border/80 bg-pi-surface/60 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-pi-fg hover:border-pi-accent/60 transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="text-pi-accent">↗</span> Quick start
          </a>
          <a
            href="#install"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full border border-pi-accent/30 bg-pi-accent/10 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-pi-accent hover:bg-pi-accent/15 transition-colors"
          >
            Skip ahead to install →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
